2026-04-21 01:30:22 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['cable pair between power supply module and control module'] hypothesis_explanation='The observed symptoms match a polarity reversal between the power supply module and the control module: the control-module red LED ("inverted cables indicator") is designed to turn on only when its input 12 V and 0 V lines are swapped relative to the power supply. The observation confirms this: PSU (+) is connected to control (−) and PSU (−) to control (+). The downstream connection from control to load is correctly polarized, so the load sees reversed polarity with respect to the actual PSU, the series diode in the load module is reverse-biased, and the lamp cannot turn on. The root cause is thus a miswired connection (polarity inversion) of the cable pair between the power supply module and control module. Reconnecting this cable pair with correct polarity (PSU + to control +, PSU − to control −) will restore proper operation.'
